description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are passionate about delivering high quality and safe care to our patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Henderson Ward is a 20 bedded Rehabilitation Unit where we admit patients from the local acute hospitals and directly from the community. We provide intensive rehabilitation for predominately older people following episodes of acute illness and injury, with the aim to ensure timely discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively promote a multi-disciplinary model, where nursing staff work closely with occupational therapists, physiotherapists and social workers; ensuring the patient are kept at the centre of decision making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Healthcare Assistant with excellent communication skills, a positive attitude, and respect for patients, carers, and colleagues to work with us to create an environment conducive to care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you are willing to go the extra mile to make patients feel important then we want to hear from you. If so please contact us on 0300 125 6117 to arrange a visit or apply online. If you would like to discuss any further details please contact the Henderson Ward on 01454 415750&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is for 23 hours per week.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
